<p><span style="color:red; font-family: monospace;">x + y == 4</span> represents the main diagonal. All points above it are represented by <span style="color:red; font-family: monospace;">x + y &gt; 4</span> and all points below it are represented by <span style="color:red; font-family: monospace;">x + y &lt; 4</span>.</p>
<p>Option-(c) reverses colors the upper portion green and the lower portion yellow and hence is incorrect.</p></div><h3 class="feedback-header faculty-answer">Accepted Answers:</h3><div class="faculty-answer"><div><div><label for="YKcdY846qqmC.0.5029260079136768.2">
                <div><link href="https://seek.onlinedegree.iitm.ac.in/static/codemirror/lib/codemirror.css" rel="stylesheet"><link href="https://seek.onlinedegree.iitm.ac.in/modules/code_tags/resources/code_tags.css" rel="stylesheet"></div><code class="codemirror-container-readonly" data-mode="python">def color_it(points):
    colored_points = dict()
    for point in points:
        x, y = point
        if x + y == 4:
            colored_points[point] = 'red'
        elif x + y &gt; 4:
            colored_points[point] = 'yellow'
        elif x + y &lt; 4:
            colored_points[point] = 'green'
   	return colored_points</code><br>
